description:
"For sale is a very nice, well maintained example of an R56 Mini Cooper S with a clean and clear Illinois title. This 2011 model has 125,900 miles and is equipped with the 6 speed MANUAL transmission. I am the third owner, I have owned for 5 years, since it had 113,000 miles. Obviously I have not put many miles on it, it was a second, ""fun"" car for me but I have maintained it regularly with high quality parts. I will gladly cover my knowledge of its maintenance and service history with any prospective buyers.

I have lightly modified the car since my ownership, including: Alta Performance intake kit, an NM Engineering Power Module, a Scan Gauge OBDII reader, stiffer wastegate spring, and an ECS Tuning rear sway bar assembly. The car has been fitted with OEM JCW (John Cooper Works) wheels fitted with Michelin Pilot Sport Cup 2 tires. These tires are sticky, summer grade tires so I would recommend removing and refitting the car with the original wheels and tires, which I have and will attach a picture in the listing. Those wheels have Continental all seasons installed that have lots of tread depth and are in great condition, but should consider being replaced due to age - I believe the date code is 2018. I may do this myself before the car sells but both sets of wheels and tires are included in the asking price.

Defects include minor exterior blemishes - a few dents, minor chips and scratches, bubbling chrome around left headlight. Interior has minor staining on headliner all the way near the hatch, can barely notice but it is there. The parking brake light is stuck on - the brake is fully disengaged but the sensor must be sticking, really a non-issue. Other than these small defects the car is in really good shape and has been a blast for me. Only selling to downsize, wish I had the space to keep it. 

Cash only, no trades. Open to a reasonable cash offer. Located in Roselle, can meet pretty much any day."

It currently has a 1961 Buick 215ci engine, with all the period correct goodies:  Offenhauser dual plane manifold, Trans Dapt H25 bell housing, Carter 500cfm carb, MG V8 Conversion Co (UK) tube headers & motor mounts, BW T-50 trans, and custom dual exhaust.  Numerous custom touches to overcome routine challenges. Engine had a $4k rebuild a few miles ago.  All new brake hydraulic and friction components.  Rust free body, no physical damage.  Comes with many extra parts to include 2 complete Buick 215ci engines, a Holley 390 cfm carb, and more. Due to age and other lifestyle changes, I have lost interest in completing and possessing this project.  It needs wiring work, paint detailing, new top, new gauges, new tires, possible trans work, and a thorough shakedown and vetting of all systems before being put on the highway. description:
"Specs:
CPU: Intel i3-10100f
Mobo: Gigabyte B460M DS3H w/ onboard wifi
RAM: 2x8gb ddr4 3200mhz cl16
GPU: Nvidia GeForce GTX 980 TI Founders Edition Gaming ACX 2.0+
PSU: Apevia Prestige 600w 80+ gold PSU
Cooler: Deepcool gamma 400 w/ white argb fan
Storage: Crucial P2 500gb NVME SSD 

Rbg on cpu cooler can be set via rgb control software Like Gigabyte Aorus Sync and set to whatever color you want. Case fans are static rainbow color. Great build for high refresh 1080p gaming on ultra settings for any game. Can handle 1440p at 60fps on most modern titles as well. Any esports title you should see around 100+ fps on highest settings. (Warzone closer to 100, games like FN seeing closer to 165)
This PC also has an excellent upgrade path. Lga 1200 motherboard socket means you can upgrade to any 10th or 11th gen intel processor down the road. GPU is still an amazing mid level gaming card and will carry you well through the gpu shortage until you feel it's time to upgrade. 2 more available ram slots as well which could easily be populated to get to a whopping 32gb. If you need more storage the case has ample room to bolt a hdd on the bottom next to the psu, and has 2 standard sata ssd mounting positions on the inside wall next to the motherboard.
Onboard wifi is a huge plus. This case is relatively small as well making this a very viable LAN PC. Could easily add aftermarket handles to the top of the case.
This thing looks stunning as well. The pictures look good but in person it's a treat for the eyes.

Asking 700, but price is negotiable.
No trades.

Feel free to reach out with any questions. 

Thanks for looking! "
